Crosshair Assistant - Crosshair Aim User Agreement

Service Scope
Crosshair Assistant - Crosshair Aim is a crosshair and training tool for FPS players and training enthusiasts. It provides a crosshair library, pro player parameter references, previews, training records, data trends, reaction training, recoil practice, sensitivity conversion, memberships, and feedback. It does not provide cheats, aimbots, scripts, injections, packet modification, or any capability that undermines fair play.

Training Tool Nature
Crosshair previews, CS2/Valorant/Apex parameter parsing, backgrounds, training scores, reaction times, hit rates, stability scores, and trend charts are for training assistance and self-recording. They do not guarantee rank, win-rate, accuracy, or any specific game performance improvement.

User Responsibility
You must comply with applicable laws, game agreements, platform rules, and tournament rules when using this app. You may not use the app for cheating, misleading others, infringing rights, mass scraping, reverse engineering, illegal transactions, or unfair play.

Membership Features
VIP members can use advanced features such as copying pro crosshair codes, random target reaction training, and sensitivity calculation, and may get priority access to future professional training data and crosshair editing enhancements. Available features may change by version and are subject to the current in-app display.

Subscription Plans
The app offers yearly and weekly auto-renewing subscriptions. Subscription prices are fetched and displayed from the App Store in real time and may vary by region, tax, exchange rate, Apple policy, or promotion.

Free Trial and Auto-Renewal
If your account is eligible for Apple’s trial offer, tapping the 3-day free trial starts a subscription through the App Store. After the trial ends, the selected plan renews automatically unless auto-renewal is turned off in Apple ID subscription settings at least 24 hours before the current period ends.

Payment, Cancellation, and Restore
Subscription payments, renewals, refunds, cancellations, and billing are handled by Apple. You can cancel in Apple ID subscription settings and tap Restore Subscription in the app to sync current Apple ID entitlements.

Data and Content Accuracy
Pro player crosshairs, sensitivities, previews, and parameters may come from public information, built-in examples, or approximate parsing. Due to game versions, devices, display ratios, in-game rendering, and personal settings, app content may differ from actual in-game results.

Feedback
You can submit issues, suggestions, or subscription questions through Feedback in Settings. Submitted content should be truthful, lawful, and clear, and should not include others’ privacy, offensive content, illegal content, or sensitive credentials.

Disclaimer
To the extent permitted by law, the app is provided as is. We are not responsible beyond the scope required by law for feature unavailability, data differences, or subscription sync delays caused by network issues, Apple services, StoreKit product configuration, device compatibility, system versions, user input errors, game updates, or third-party platform rule changes.

Agreement Updates
We may update this agreement due to product features, subscription capability, laws, regulations, or platform policies. Updated terms will be displayed in the app. Continued use means you understand and accept the updated terms.
